  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 05:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] V5a Backtest Complete \u2014 min_bias=45 Confirmed as Sweet Spot\n\n**Task:** Build V5a backtest \u2014 replay all V3+ trades through min_bias filters at different thresholds to find the optimal cutoff.\n\n**Backtest Results (78 V3+ trades, V4.1 hours, Mar 25-30):**\n\n| min_bias | WR | Trades/day | $/day ($11) | $/day ($16) | Sharpe |\n|----------|-----|-----------|-------------|-------------|--------|\n| 0 (current) | 77.1% | 5.8 | $34.80 | $50.40 | 1.56 |\n| 30 | 79.3% | 4.8 | $31.20 | $45.10 | 1.59 |\n| 40 | 78.3% | 3.8 | $23.80 | $34.50 | 1.34 |\n| **45** | **85.0%** | **3.3** | **$25.70** | **$37.20** | **1.79** |\n| 50 | 90.9% | 1.8 | $16.50 | $23.90 | 1.93 |\n| 55 | 100% | 0.5 | $5.50 | $8.00 | \u2014 |\n\n**Why 45 is the sweet spot:**\n1. WR jumps 8pp (77\u219285%) \u2014 enters high-confidence territory\n2. Sharpe is highest practical value (1.79) \u2014 min_bias=50 has higher Sharpe but too few trades\n3. The eliminated trades (bias 30-45) are 4W/5L = 44% WR \u2014 actively losing money\n4. At consolidated capital ($16/trade), $37/day still exceeds Phase 2 target\n5. Daily P&L only drops $9/day despite cutting 43% of trades \u2014 those trades were destroying edge\n\n**Why NOT 50:** 90.9% WR looks amazing but 1.8 trades/day = only $16.50/day. Below Phase 2 threshold at current capital. The extra 6pp WR doesn't compensate for losing half the remaining trades.\n\n**Patch written:** `patches/v5a-min-bias-45.patch.md` \u2014 ready for deployment Apr 6.\n\n**Combined V5 roadmap:**\n- V5a (Apr 6): min_bias=45 \u2192 +8pp WR, better Sharpe\n- V5b (Apr 13): OBI weighting + MACD inversion \u2192 targeting 88%+ WR (needs more data)\n- V5c (Apr 20): Liquidation detector + V2 copy signal integration\n- HL consolidation: when PM balance hits $1,000\n\n**Decision:** Backtest confirms min_bias=45. Patch ready. Deploy Apr 6 after V4.1 stability week. No early deployment \u2014 the $9/day cost of waiting = insurance against overfitting.\n\n**Next P3:** Design V5b conviction rewrite (OBI-weighted scoring). Need to build matching logic that aligns TRADE SIGNAL log entries to outcome JSONL entries for the OBI cross-tab backtest.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 05:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] OBI is the Only Indicator That Matters \u2014 V5 Conviction Rewrite\n\n**Task:** Analyze per-indicator performance to find which indicators actually predict wins, and optimize entry parameters.\n\n**Data:** 140 matched trades (signal \u2192 outcome) from March, including all V4.1 era trades.\n\n**Finding 1 \u2014 OBI is the DOMINANT indicator:**\n| Condition | WR | n | Delta |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| OBI\u2705 (all hours) | 65% | 74 | +13pp vs OBI\u274c |\n| OBI\u274c (all hours) | 52% | 66 | coin flip |\n| OBI\u2705 + V4.1 hours | **88%** | 24 | +36pp vs OBI\u274c |\n| OBI\u274c + V4.1 hours | **52%** | 23 | breakeven |\n\nOBI alone accounts for almost ALL of the edge in V4.1 hours. When OBI confirms order flow aligns with our contrarian YES, we win 88% of the time. When it doesn't, we're flipping coins.\n\n**Findin",
